  <title>GLib.chdir</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function chdir(path: String): Number(gint) {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_chdir()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>A wrapper for the POSIX chdir() function. The function changes the
current directory of the process to <code>path</code>.</p>  <p>See your C library manual for more details about chdir().</p>
  <p>Since 2.8</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>path</code></title>
  <p>a pathname in the GLib file name encoding (UTF-8 on Windows)</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>0 on success, -1 if an error occurred.</p>
